                                                   Systems as Attack Vectors — Task-Wise Answers

Task 1 — Introduction
• No answer required (intro only)

Task 2 — Definition of System

Can cyber attacks happen without victim intervention (Yea/Nay)? → Yea

Can a breach of just a single system lead to disastrous consequences (Yea/Nay)? → Yea

Task 3 — System-Focused Concepts
• What is the term for a security flaw that can be exploited to breach a system? → Vulnerability
• What is the name of the attack when malware comes from a trusted app or library? → Supply Chain

Task 4 — Vulnerabilities
• What is the CVE for the critical SharePoint vulnerability dubbed “ToolShell”? → CVE-2025-53770
• How would you respond to a detected vulnerability on your system? → Patch

Task 5 — Fixing Misconfigurations
• Can a system patch or software update fix the misconfigurations (Yea/Nay)? → Nay
• Which activity involves an authorized cyber attack to detect the misconfigurations? → Penetration Testing

Task 6 — Practice Challenges
• What flag did you receive after completing the “Systems at Risk” challenge? → THM{patch_or_reconfigure?}
• What flag did you receive after completing the “Remediation Plan” challenge? → THM{best_systems_defender!}

Task 7 — Conclusion
• No extra answers (congratulatory text)
